===Etymology===
Latin ''abdomen'' (a word of uncertain etymol.): compare French ''abdomen''
===Noun===
#''(Anatomy):'' The belly, or that part of the body between the [[thorax]] and the [[pelvis]]. Also, the cavity of the belly, which is lined by the [[peritoneum]], and contains the stomach, [[bowels]], and other [[viscera]]. In man, often restricted to the part between the [[diaphragm]] and the [[commencement]] of the pelvis, the [[remainder]] being called the [[pelvic]] cavity.
#:'''Example'''
#:*He was all bent over complaining of pains in the abdomen.
#''(Zoölogy):'' The [[posterior]] section of the body, behind the thorax, in insects, [[crustaceans]], and other [[Arthropoda]].

